Data Description¶

Context¶

Since 2008, Airbnb has been a platform for travelers having another option of staying in local hosts’ home different from hotel and resort

Content¶

The original source is from the database of Airbnb’s websit opened to the public. The csv file includes all needed information to find out more about hosts, geographical availability, necessary metrics

Data Visualization¶

Using plots and excel to produce charts
1.Get correlation between different variables
2.The rental accommodation density for areas (bar chart,distribution map, heat map)
3.Price and areas(Price Density and Distribution, Price distribution on map)
4.Room type and minimum nights
5.Customer Churn
6.Accommodation on rent

The Column descriptions¶

neighbourhood_group:location
neighbourhood:area
room_type:listing space type
minimum_nights:amount of nights minimum
number_of_reviews:number of reviews
last_review:latest review
reviews_per_month:number of reviews per month
calculated_host_listings_count:amount of listing per host
availability_365:number of days when listing is available for booking

Room Types¶

The percentage of housing is surprisingly over "a half". Usually, traveller prefers a shared room or private room for short days and tenant prefers a department or private room for long days.However, the hosts on Airbnb seem to offer more apartments than rooms. Confirm this by checking the minimum nights.

✦ The percentages of accommodation for traveller and tenant¶

  1. There is 96% of house/room sources has a minimum night of within 2 weeks and 2 weeks is usually the limited day for travellers on a trip (depends on holidays given by the company). Only 4% of the hosts open their property to guests for long-time stay.

Customer Churn¶

✦ From the report of availability_365 has 1119 (11.3%) zeros, Airbnb may lose the source of host or the owners would temporarily close. Take a look at the data by areas, room types and prices.Lodgings are closed by guests checking in or hosts stopping using Airbnb could cause the unavailable status.

  1. The number of the hosts stopping using Airbnb is 327, and Customer Churn rate is 3.29%
In [42]:
df=pd.read_csv("listingsRoc.csv")
df0=df[df['availability_365']==0]
losing=df0[df0["last_review"].isnull()]
print(len(losing),len(losing)/len(df))

327 0.03290731609137567

Of all of 327 data, take a look at the percentages and numbers for the columns of areas, room types and nimimum nights

  1. Daan(大安 23%), Zhongshan(中山 14%) and Xinyi(信義 13%) District lose the most share counting for a total of 50%, followed by Wanhua 萬華 of 10%.
  2. There are 188 (58%) private rooms closing to people and 105 (32%) apartments are unavailiable.
  3. The lodgings with minimum nights of 1-3 lose the largest share.
